   "source": [
    "# Energy Fraud Detection — Colab Runner\n",
    "\n",
    "**Before running**: Make sure your Colab runtime is set to **GPU** (`Runtime → Change runtime type → T4 GPU`)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 1 — Mount Google Drive and set the working directory\n",
    "\n",
    "Upload the repo folder to your Drive first, then update `REPO_PATH` below to match its location."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from google.colab import drive\n",
    "drive.mount('/content/drive')\n",
    "\n",
    "import os, sys\n",
    "\n",
    "# *** UPDATE THIS PATH to wherever you placed the repo folder in your Drive ***\n",
    "REPO_PATH = '/content/drive/MyDrive/Energy-Fraud-Detection-System-based-on-Deep-Learning'\n",
    "\n",
    "os.chdir(REPO_PATH)\n",
    "sys.path.insert(0, REPO_PATH)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Working directory:', os.getcwd())\n",
    "print('sys.path[0]:', sys.path[0])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 2 — Install dependencies\n",
    "\n",
    "Run once per Colab session. Takes ~3 minutes."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%%capture install_log\n",
    "!pip install \\\n",
    "    'scikit-learn==1.3.2' \\\n",
    "    'imbalanced-learn==0.11.0' \\\n",
    "    polars pyarrow tqdm \\\n",
    "    pytorch-lightning torchmetrics \\\n",
    "    xgboost shap\n",
    "# torch, numpy, pandas, matplotlib are already present in the Colab base image\n",
    "print('Installation complete.')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 3 — Verify data files are present\n",
    "\n",
    "The pipeline expects processed CSV files in `data/processed/`.  \n",
    "If that folder is empty, run `src/features/build_features.py` first (see README)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pathlib\n",
    "\n",
    "processed = pathlib.Path('data/processed')\n",
    "files = sorted(processed.glob('*.csv')) if processed.exists() else []\n",
    "\n",
    "if not files:\n",
    "    print('ERROR: data/processed/ is empty or missing.')\n",
    "    print('Run the preprocessing step first (see README).')\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(f'Found {len(files)} CSV file(s) in data/processed/:')\n",
    "    for f in files:\n",
    "        print(f'  {f.name}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 4 — Enable inline plots"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "import matplotlib\n",
